               Ʋch hath been the reſtleſſe ſpirit of Malignity in ſome amongſt us, as if they meant to out-vie the manifold providence and goodneſſe of God by an unwearyed reiteration of new experiments, whether the Watchman of Iſrael bee yet awake, for the protection and preſervation of his people: from which Atheiſticall

principle, ungodly and unreaſonable men, have rouſed up their almoſt deſpairing ſpirits, to new and more vigorous actings of their miſchiefe. And hence was it that notwithſtanding the manifeſt hand of God in diſcovering their former wickedneſſes, and bringing them upon their owne heads, once and againe in this County, and in other parts of the Kingdome;
